        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 7:13AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 712 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rockwell, or 10 miles northeast of Downtown Concord, moving east at
55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Asheboro, Albemarle, Troy, Badin Lake, Biscoe, Seagrove, High Rock
Lake, Badin, Denton, and Star.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon EDT for
central North Carolina.</instruction>
